        System.out.println(temp);

        temp = height * width;
        System.out.println(temp);
    }
}
```

This program first calculates the product of `height` and `width`, then multiplies it by `2` times the sum of `height` and `width`. The result is assigned to `temp`.

Please replace the values of `height` and `width` with your actual measurements. 

The output will be:

```
30
50
```

